channel.title: Papers with Code: Latest (unofficial)
channel.description: As a disclaimer, this is an unofficial feed and has no affiliation with Papers with Code.

item.title: Invariant Collaborative Filtering to Popularity Distribution Shift
item.description: Collaborative Filtering (CF) models, despite their great success, suffer from severe performance drops due to popularity distribution shifts, where these changes are ubiquitous and inevitable in real-world scenarios.

item.title: The out-of-sample $R^2$: estimation and inference
item.description: Out-of-sample prediction is the acid test of predictive models, yet an independent test dataset is often not available for assessment of the prediction error.

item.title: Evaluation of Data Augmentation and Loss Functions in Semantic Image Segmentation for Drilling Tool Wear Detection
item.description: Furthermore, models are trained on image tiles of different sizes, and augmentation techniques of varying intensities are deployed.

item.title: Long-Tailed Partial Label Learning via Dynamic Rebalancing
item.description: The straightforward combination of LT and PLL, i. e., LT-PLL, suffers from a fundamental dilemma: LT methods build upon a given class distribution that is unavailable in PLL, and the performance of PLL is severely influenced in long-tailed context.

item.title: AIOSA: An approach to the automatic identification of obstructive sleep apnea events based on deep learning
item.description: Obstructive Sleep Apnea Syndrome (OSAS) is the most common sleep-related breathing disorder.

item.title: Tackling Bias in the Dice Similarity Coefficient: Introducing nDSC for White Matter Lesion Segmentation
item.description: This work describes a detailed analysis of the recently proposed normalised Dice Similarity Coefficient (nDSC) for binary segmentation tasks as an adaptation of DSC which scales the precision at a fixed recall rate to tackle this bias.

item.title: Controllability-Aware Unsupervised Skill Discovery
item.description: One of the key capabilities of intelligent agents is the ability to discover useful skills without external supervision.

item.title: Span-based Named Entity Recognition by Generating and Compressing Information
item.description: For one type of IB model, we incorporate two unsupervised generative components, span reconstruction and synonym generation, into a span-based NER system.

item.title: Unbinned Profiled Unfolding
item.description: We propose a new machine learning-based unfolding method that results in an unbinned differential cross section and can profile nuisance parameters.

item.title: On Penalty-based Bilevel Gradient Descent Method
item.description: Bilevel optimization enjoys a wide range of applications in hyper-parameter optimization, meta-learning and reinforcement learning.

item.title: Short-Term Aggregated Residential Load Forecasting using BiLSTM and CNN-BiLSTM
item.description: Using a publicly available dataset consisting of 38 homes, the BiLSTM and CNN-BiLSTM models are trained to forecast the aggregated active power demand for each hour within a 24 hr.

item.title: EVC: Towards Real-Time Neural Image Compression with Mask Decay
item.description: Both mask decay and residual representation learning greatly improve the RD performance of our scalable encoder.

item.title: A deep convolutional neural network for salt-and-pepper noise removal using selective convolutional blocks
item.description: In this paper, we proposed a deep CNN model, namely SeConvNet, to suppress SAP noise in gray-scale and color images.

item.title: Toward Degree Bias in Embedding-Based Knowledge Graph Completion
item.description: It aims to predict unseen edges by learning representations for all the entities and relations in a KG.

item.title: CGA-PoseNet: Camera Pose Regression via a 1D-Up Approach to Conformal Geometric Algebra
item.description: This 1D-Up approach to CGA can be employed to overcome the dichotomy between translational and orientational components in camera pose regression in a compact and elegant way.

item.title: CEN-HDR: Computationally Efficient neural Network for real-time High Dynamic Range imaging
item.description: High dynamic range (HDR) imaging is still a challenging task in modern digital photography.

item.title: Predicting the cardinality of a reduced Gr√∂bner basis
item.description: We use ansatz neural network models to predict key metrics of complexity for Gr\"obner bases of binomial ideals.

item.title: Tensor Generalized Canonical Correlation Analysis
item.description: Regularized Generalized Canonical Correlation Analysis (RGCCA) is a general statistical framework for multi-block data analysis.

item.title: A SWAT-based Reinforcement Learning Framework for Crop Management
item.description: Crop management involves a series of critical, interdependent decisions or actions in a complex and highly uncertain environment, which exhibit distinct spatial and temporal variations.

item.title: Making Substitute Models More Bayesian Can Enhance Transferability of Adversarial Examples
item.description: In this paper, by contrast, we opt for the diversity in substitute models and advocate to attack a Bayesian model for achieving desirable transferability.

item.title: Adjacent-level Feature Cross-Fusion with 3D CNN for Remote Sensing Image Change Detection
item.description: First, through the inner fusion property of 3D convolution, we design a new feature fusion way that can simultaneously extract and fuse the feature information from bi-temporal images.

item.title: Plan-then-Seam: Towards Efficient Table-to-Text Generation
item.description: Table-to-text generation aims at automatically generating text to help people conveniently obtain salient information in tables.

item.title: Dual Memory Units with Uncertainty Regulation for Weakly Supervised Video Anomaly Detection
item.description: To address this issue, we propose an Uncertainty Regulated Dual Memory Units (UR-DMU) model to learn both the representations of normal data and discriminative features of abnormal data.

item.title: DOMINO: Domain-aware Loss for Deep Learning Calibration
item.description: Deep learning has achieved the state-of-the-art performance across medical imaging tasks; however, model calibration is often not considered.

item.title: Generalized Video Anomaly Event Detection: Systematic Taxonomy and Comparison of Deep Models
item.description: Video Anomaly Event Detection (VAED) is the core technology of intelligent surveillance systems aiming to temporally or spatially locate anomalous events in videos.

item.title: Unified Functional Hashing in Automatic Machine Learning
item.description: In this paper, we show that large efficiency gains can be obtained by employing a fast unified functional hash, especially through the functional equivalence caching technique, which we also present.

item.title: XFL: A High Performace, Lightweighted Federated Learning Framework
item.description: This paper introduces XFL, an industrial-grade federated learning project.

item.title: Robot Synesthesia: A Sound and Emotion Guided AI Painter
item.description: For speech, we decouple speech into its transcribed text and the tone of the speech.

item.title: Better Diffusion Models Further Improve Adversarial Training
item.description: It has been recognized that the data generated by the denoising diffusion probabilistic model (DDPM) improves adversarial training.

item.title: Principled and Efficient Motif Finding for Structure Learning in Lifted Graphical Models
item.description: We present the first principled approach for mining structural motifs in lifted graphical models, languages that blend first-order logic with probabilistic models, which uses a stochastic process to measure the similarity of entities in the data.

item.title: Detecting Contextomized Quotes in News Headlines by Contrastive Learning
item.description: Quotes are critical for establishing credibility in news articles.

item.title: Robust Question Answering against Distribution Shifts with Test-Time Adaptation: An Empirical Study
item.description: To answer this question, we evaluate test-time adaptation (TTA) to improve a model after deployment.

item.title: Reversible Vision Transformers
item.description: Reversible Vision Transformers achieve a reduced memory footprint of up to 15. 5x at roughly identical model complexity, parameters and accuracy, demonstrating the promise of reversible vision transformers as an efficient backbone for hardware resource limited training regimes.

item.title: A Transformer-based Response Evaluator for Open-Domain Spoken Conversation
item.description: First, we collect a corpus of Athena conversations with live human traffic, where potential responses from all enabled response generators are logged and subsequently annotated for response quality.

item.title: RayNet: A Simulation Platform for Developing Reinforcement Learning-Driven Network Protocols
item.description: In this paper, we introduce RayNet, a scalable and adaptable simulation framework for the development of learning-based network protocols.

item.title: Hierarchical Generative Adversarial Imitation Learning with Mid-level Input Generation for Autonomous Driving on Urban Environments
item.description: The proposed hGAIL consists of an hierarchical Adversarial Imitation Learning architecture composed of two main modules: the GAN (Generative Adversarial Nets) which generates the Bird's-Eye View (BEV) representation mainly from the images of three frontal cameras of the vehicle, and the GAIL which learns to control the vehicle based mainly on the BEV predictions from the GAN as input. Our experiments have shown that GAIL exclusively from cameras (without BEV) fails to even learn the task, while hGAIL, after training, was able to autonomously navigate successfully in all intersections of the city.

item.title: Massively Multilingual Language Models for Cross Lingual Fact Extraction from Low Resource Indian Languages
item.description: Cross Lingual Information Extraction aims at extracting factual information in the form of English triples from low resource Indian Language text.

item.title: ManiSkill2: A Unified Benchmark for Generalizable Manipulation Skills
item.description: Generalizable manipulation skills, which can be composed to tackle long-horizon and complex daily chores, are one of the cornerstones of Embodied AI.

item.title: Generating a Structured Summary of Numerous Academic Papers: Dataset and Method
item.description: Existing MDS datasets usually focus on producing the structureless summary covering a few input documents.

item.title: Zero-Shot Learning for Requirements Classification: An Exploratory Study
item.description: Principal ideas-results: To address this challenge, this paper proposes an approach that employs the embedding-based unsupervised Zero-Shot Learning (ZSL) technique to perform requirements classification.

item.title: Weakly Supervised Anomaly Detection: A Survey
item.description: Anomaly detection (AD) is a crucial task in machine learning with various applications, such as detecting emerging diseases, identifying financial frauds, and detecting fake news.

item.title: Learning to Select Pivotal Samples for Meta Re-weighting
item.description: In this paper, we study how to learn to identify such a meta sample set from a large, imperfect training set, that is subsequently cleaned and used to optimize performance in the meta re-weighting setting.

item.title: Global Constraints with Prompting for Zero-Shot Event Argument Classification
item.description: In this work, we propose to use global constraints with prompting to effectively tackles event argument classification without any annotation and task-specific training.

item.title: GCI: A (G)raph (C)oncept (I)nterpretation Framework
item.description: Explainable AI (XAI) underwent a recent surge in research on concept extraction, focusing on extracting human-interpretable concepts from Deep Neural Networks.

item.title: Gentlest ascent dynamics on manifolds defined by adaptively sampled point-clouds
item.description: Finding saddle points of dynamical systems is an important problem in practical applications such as the study of rare events of molecular systems.

item.title: Real-Time Visual Feedback to Guide Benchmark Creation: A Human-and-Metric-in-the-Loop Workflow
item.description: In pursuit of creating better benchmarks, we propose VAIDA, a novel benchmark creation paradigm for NLP, that focuses on guiding crowdworkers, an under-explored facet of addressing benchmark idiosyncrasies.

item.title: rMultiNet: An R Package For Multilayer Networks Analysis
item.description: This paper develops an R package rMultiNet to analyze multilayer network data.

item.title: Hyperparameter Search Is All You Need For Training-Agnostic Backdoor Robustness
item.description: We demonstrate how to use our metric to estimate the robustness of models to backdoor attacks.

item.title: In-Context Learning with Many Demonstration Examples
item.description: Based on EVALM, we scale up the size of examples efficiently in both instruction tuning and in-context learning to explore the boundary of the benefits from more annotated data.

item.title: Gaussian Process-Gated Hierarchical Mixtures of Experts
item.description: Further, the experts are also built with Gaussian processes and provide predictions that depend on test data.
